{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7a3bdbef-1d4c-4c85-bf4b-bd26d9730d58","content":"The working directory is empty, so I'll provide the recommended setup from MSTest knowledge:\n\n## 1. Simplest project file with MSTest.Sdk\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.7\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\n`MSTest.Sdk` bundles MSTest runner, framework, and analyzers — no extra `<PackageReference>` needed.\n\n## 2. Enable parallel execution\n\nAdd a `.runsettings` file or an assembly-level attribute. The simplest way:\n\n```csharp\n// Usings.cs (or AssemblyInfo.cs)\n[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.MethodLevel)]\n```\n\nThis runs all test methods in parallel across classes.\n\n## 3. Run database tests sequentially\n\nDecorate your integration test class with `[DoNotParallelize]`:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Can_Insert_Record() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Can_Read_After_Write() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\nAll methods in that class will run sequentially and won't overlap with other parallel tests.\n\n---\n\n**Summary:**\n| Concern | Mechanism |\n|---------|-----------|\n| SDK | `MSTest.Sdk/3.7` (no extra packages) |\n| Parallel by default | `[assembly: Parallelize]` |\n| Sequential opt-out | `[DoNotParallelize]` on class |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c3c47804-a898-4c8a-afb5-a3165c4282c3","outputTokens":410,"requestId":"BD16:3113E4:1F0B493:231246F:6A07CEF4"},"id":"641de793-87cf-4454-b48c-3c8092a214d9","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:57:17.417Z","parentId":"7edff59f-b535-441f-8353-eab5bfb21712"}
